POLOKWANE – More wet weather is expected in the city this week with thunderstorms and showers forecast. While the week will start off warm, milder conditions are expected from Wednesday (February 8) onwards with highs of 25ºC. AccuWeather has forecast a 25%-68% chance of thunderstorms with majority of the rain expected from Thursday into the weekend.  Temperatures are expected to increase over the weekend with highs of 28ºC and 29ºC.  Partly cloudy to cloudy conditions will persist throughout the week. 